&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;GitLab is the intelligent orchestration platform for DevSecOps. GitLab enables organizations to increase developer productivity, improve operational efficiency, reduce security and compliance risk, and accelerate digital transformation. More than 50 million registered users and more than 50% of the Fortune 100* trust GitLab to ship better, more secure software faster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The same principles built into our products are reflected in how our team works: we embrace AI as a core productivity multiplier, with all team members expected to incorporate AI into their daily workflows to drive efficiency, innovation, and impact. GitLab is where careers accelerate, innovation flourishes, and every voice is valued. Our high-performance culture is driven by our values&amp;nbsp;and continuous knowledge exchange, enabling our team members to reach their full potential while collaborating with industry leaders to solve complex problems. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OuZIb5zszQI&quot;&gt;Co-create the future with us&lt;/a&gt; as we build technology that transforms how the world develops software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*&lt;em&gt;Fortune 500® is a registered trademark of Fortune Media IP Limited, used under license. Claim based on GitLab data. Fortune 100 refers to the top 20% ranked companies in the 2025 Fortune 500 list, published in June 2025. Fortune and Fortune Media IP Limited are not affiliated with, and do not endorse products or services of GitLab.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;An overview of this role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Solutions Architect, you will help GitLab scale specialized expertise across our go-to-market teams by guiding complex customer conversations related to the Microsoft ecosystem. This role sits within the Solutions Architect Center of Excellence and reports to the Senior Director, Center of Excellence. You will help shape how GitLab is positioned in strategic Microsoft-centered accounts, run technical evaluations that validate GitLab as an AI-powered DevSecOps platform, and contribute reusable patterns, demos, and field guidance that improve how we engage customers at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide guidance for technical discovery with prospects and customers to assess current Microsoft ecosystem investments, development workflows, security needs, and platform requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design solutions that show how GitLab supports secure, scalable software delivery across the software lifecycle, from planning and code management through deployment and monitoring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver tailored demonstrations and technical presentations that map customer needs to GitLab&#39;s platform capabilities, including AI-powered DevSecOps use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate proofs of concept and proofs of value end to end, guiding stakeholders through evaluation plans, technical validation, and solution fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales, Customer Success, and Solutions Architecture to advance strategic customer engagements and extend specialized expertise across the broader go-to-market motion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Marketing and Field Enablement on building up GitLab&#39;s position relative to GitHub in clear, evidence-based terms while also identifying ways GitLab can work alongside existing Microsoft products in customer environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create reusable assets, technical frameworks, and field guidance that help teams apply Microsoft-focused expertise consistently across opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product and Engineering to relay customer feedback, field insights, and technical patterns that can influence future product direction and enablement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in customer-facing technical roles that combine architecture guidance, solution validation, and strategic customer engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the Microsoft ecosystem, including how customers use Microsoft and GitHub products within software delivery environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical background in modern software development or operations, including continuous integration and continuous delivery, DevSecOps practices, and related tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of cloud computing concepts and architectures, including how cloud services enable secure and scalable application delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to design and communicate architectures that span multiple teams and stages of the software lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skill in facilitating workshops, technical discovery sessions, and evaluation programs with audiences that range from practitioners to executive stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strength in communication, relationship building, and stakeholder management across Sales, Product, Engineering, and customer teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Openness to applying transferable experience from adjacent platforms or environments if you can translate technical depth into customer outcomes in a clear, practical way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Solutions Architecture Center of Excellence is a globally distributed team operating across specialized roles including Subject Matter Experts, Demo Architects, and Business Value Consultants. The team exists to deliver expertise at scale across GitLab&#39;s go-to-market motion, helping customer-facing teams address complex technical and business questions with repeatable, high-value guidance. This team works globally across regions and partners closely with Sales, Customer Success, Product, and Engineering to strengthen technical strategy, reusable assets, and field execution. For this role, the focus is on helping GitLab engage Microsoft-centered environments with clear platform positioning, practical architecture guidance, and technical credibility.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The base salary range for this role’s listed level is currently for residents of the&amp;nbsp;United States only. This range is intended to reflect the role&#39;s base salary rate in locations throughout the US.&amp;nbsp;Grade level and salary ranges are determined through interviews and a review of education, experience, knowledge, skills, abilities of the applicant, equity with other team members, alignment with market data,&amp;nbsp;and geographic location.&amp;nbsp;The base salary range does not include any bonuses, equity, or benefits. See more information on our &lt;a class=&quot;waffle-rich-text-link&quot; href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-link=&quot;https://bit.ly/GLBeneUS&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-style=&quot;font-size:12px;color:#1155cc;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:underline;font-family:&#39;&#39;Arial&#39;&#39;;font-style:normal;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;&quot;&gt;benefits&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-formula-bar-text-style=&quot;font-size:12px;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;font-family:&#39;Arial&#39;;font-style:normal;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;&quot;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;waffle-rich-text-link&quot; href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/stock-options/&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-link=&quot;https://bit.ly/GLequity&quot; data-sheets-formula-bar-text-style=&quot;font-size:12px;color:#1155cc;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:underline;font-family:&#39;&#39;Arial&#39;&#39;;font-style:normal;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;&quot;&gt;equity&lt;/a&gt;. Sales roles are also eligible for incentive pay targeted at up to 100% of the offered base salary.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;United States Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$137,400&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$231,300 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How GitLab Supports Full-Time Employees&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/&quot;&gt;Benefits to support your health, finances, and well-being&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/people-group/time-off-and-absence/time-off-types/#flexible-paid-time-off-pto&quot;&gt;Flexible Paid Time Off&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/company/culture/inclusion/tmrg-tmag/&quot;&gt;Team Member Resource Groups&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/stock-options/&quot;&gt;Equity Compensation &amp;amp; Employee Stock Purchase Plan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/people-group/learning-and-development/growth-and-development/&quot;&gt;Growth and Development Fund&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/#parental-leave&quot;&gt;Parental Leave&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that we welcome interest from candidates with varying levels of experience; many successful candidates do not meet every single requirement. Additionally, studies have shown that people from &lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/inclusion/#examples-of-select-underrepresented-groups&quot;&gt;underrepresented groups&lt;/a&gt; are less likely to apply to a job unless they meet every single qualification. If you&#39;re excited about this role, please apply and allow our recruiters to assess your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Country Hiring Guidelines: &lt;/strong&gt;GitLab hires new team members in countries around the world. All of our roles are remote, however some roles may carry specific location-based eligibility requirements. Our Talent Acquisition team can help answer any questions about location after starting the recruiting process.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Privacy Policy: &lt;/strong&gt;Please review our &lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/hiring/candidate-faq/recruitment-privacy-policy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Recruitment Privacy Policy.&lt;/a&gt; Your privacy is important to us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitLab is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. GitLab’s policies and practices relating to recruitment, employment, career development and advancement, promotion, and retirement are based solely on merit, regardless of race, color, religion, ancestry, sex (including pregnancy, lactation, sexual orientation, gender identity, or gender expression), national origin, age, citizenship, marital status, mental or physical disability, genetic information (including family medical history), discharge status from the military, protected veteran status (which includes disabled veterans, recently separated veterans, active duty wartime or campaign badge veterans, and Armed Forces service medal veterans), or any other basis protected by law. GitLab will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics. See also&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/people-policies/inc-usa/#equal-employment-opportunity-policy&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;GitLab’s EEO Policy&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/labor-and-employment-notices/#eeoc-us-equal-employment-opportunity-commission-notices&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;EEO is the Law&lt;/a&gt;. If you have a disability or special need that requires&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/people-policies/inc-usa/#reasonable-accommodation&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;accommodation&lt;/a&gt;, please let us know during the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/hiring/interviewing/#adjustments-to-our-interview-process&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;recruiting process&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
